## Tech Stack (Locked)

- **Framework:** Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 + design tokens from `07.5-design-direction/`
- **Components:** Shadcn UI (themed with AirThere colors)
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod validation
- **Dates:** date-fns
- **Data:** Mock service layer (swappable for real APIs)
- **Testing:** Vitest + React Testing Library + axe-core
- **Deployment:** Vercel

---

## The Five Experience Principles (Non-Negotiable)

Every line of code must serve these:

### 1. Anticipatory Calm
The best technology is felt, never seen. Proactive, predictive, invisible.
- Animations purposeful (never decorative)
- Transitions smooth
- Form layouts intuitive
- Error messages rare and helpful
- Abundant white space

### 2. Radical Transparency
Every cost, delay, option visible. No dark patterns.
- Show actual prices (no hidden fees)
- Display all costs upfront
- Explain delays clearly
- Never manipulate options

### 3. Family Integrity
The family unit is sacred. Never separate, never surprise.
- Family groups stay together
- Seating locks in place
- Rebooking maintains group
- Itineraries are shared

### 4. Graduated Trust
AI earns autonomy through competence. Copilot → Curator → Agent.
- Show what AI is about to do before it does it
- Give users override capability
- Build trust through transparency

### 5. Journey Continuity
One identity, one context, zero repetition.
- User state persists across screens
- Preferences remembered
- No re-explaining of information
- Context carries through

---

## The Three Personas

Design for these humans. Every screen has persona adaptations.

### PERSONA-01: Alexandra — Premium Traveler
- 45-62, UHNW ($5M+), C-suite, 15-30+ trips/year, $8k-$30k+ per ticket
- Psychology: Status marker. Invisible seamlessness expected. Zero tolerance for mediocrity.
- Key Needs: Biometric-first, invisible context, autonomy with override, premium visual language, privacy
- Design Tone: Elegant restraint, sophisticated blue, premium whitespace, status symbols, subtle confidence

### PERSONA-02: Marcus — Business Traveler
- 35-55, 12-25+ trips/year, corporate $15k-$40k/year, tech/finance/consulting
- Psychology: Control-seeking but time-starved. Perfect info without research. Policy-conscious.
- Key Needs: Sub-90-second booking, unified visibility, auto disruption recovery, lounge consistency, expense reconciliation
- Design Tone: Efficient, time-saving indicators, clear metrics, policy badges, quick-tap shortcuts

### PERSONA-03: The Chen Family — Leisure/Family Traveler
- Parents 35-50, 2-4 kids, 3-5 trips/year, $4k-$8k per trip, price-conscious
- Psychology: Transparency and honesty. Coordination efficiency. Family bonding focus. Guided support.
- Key Needs: Total cost transparency, family group booking, seating guarantee, packing intelligence, coordination tools, deal alerts
- Design Tone: Warm, family-centric, helpful guidance, clear cost breakdowns, child-friendly content

