## Coding Conventions

### TypeScript
- **Strict mode always** — No `any` types
- **All props fully typed** — Explicit interfaces for every component
- **Discriminated unions** — For state (`{ status: 'loading' } | { status: 'success'; data: T }`)

```typescript
interface FlightSearchProps {
  onSearch: (params: SearchParams) => Promise<void>;
  isLoading: boolean;
}

interface SearchParams {
  from: string;
  to: string;
  departDate: Date;
  returnDate?: Date;
  passengers: number;
}
```

### Components
- **Server Components by default** — Client Components only when needed (interactivity, hooks)
- **Mobile-first responsive** — Use Tailwind `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- **Accessibility required** — Semantic HTML, ARIA labels, keyboard navigation
- **States always handled** — Loading, error, empty states for every component

```typescript
interface FlightCardProps {
  flight: Flight;
  isSelected: boolean;
  onSelect: (flightId: string) => void;
}

export function FlightCard({
  flight,
  isSelected,
  onSelect,
}: FlightCardProps) {
  return (
    <button
      onClick={() => onSelect(flight.id)}
      className={`card ${isSelected ? 'ring-2 ring-primary-500' : ''}`}
      aria-pressed={isSelected}
    >
      {/* Content */}
    </button>
  );
}
```

### Styling
- **Never use default Shadcn colors** — Apply AirThere theme from `design-tokens.json`
- **No placeholder grays** — Use surface tokens (primary-50, primary-100, neutral-200, etc.)
- **OKLCH is canonical** — Use `oklch(...)` values, not hex approximations
- **Consistent border-radius** — From design tokens (usually 8px or 12px)
- **Test dark mode** — Every component must have `dark:` variants

```tsx
// CORRECT: Using AirThere tokens
<button className="bg-primary-500 text-white hover:bg-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-400 dark:hover:bg-primary-300">
  Book Now
</button>

// WRONG: Generic Tailwind colors (do not use)
<button className="bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700">
  Book Now
</button>
```

### Data & Mock Services
- **Service interface abstraction** — Every API has an interface; mock is swappable
- **Realistic data** — Real airline codes (AA, BA, SQ), airport codes (JFK, LHR, SIN), authentic prices
- **No Lorem Ipsum** — Use actual travel content: real cities, airlines, routes

```typescript
interface FlightService {
  search(params: SearchParams): Promise<Flight[]>;
  getDetails(flightId: string): Promise<FlightDetails>;
}

class MockFlightService implements FlightService {
  async search(params: SearchParams): Promise<Flight[]> {
    return getMockFlightsForRoute(params.from, params.to);
  }
}
```

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- **Semantic HTML** — `<button>`, `<input>`, `<label>`, not `<div onclick>`
- **ARIA labels** — Complex components need `role`, `aria-label`, `aria-describedby`
- **Focus management** — Visible focus rings, logical tab order
- **Color contrast** — Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text
- **Touch targets** — Minimum 44×44pt
- **Keyboard navigation** — All interactions accessible via keyboard

```tsx
<button
  onClick={handleClick}
  className="focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none"
  aria-label="Book this flight"
  aria-describedby="flight-price"
>
  Book <span id="flight-price">$892</span>
</button>
```

### Responsiveness
- **Mobile first** — Design for 320px, enhance for larger screens
- **Test at breakpoints** — 320px, 768px (tablet), 1024px (desktop)
- **Touch-friendly** — 44pt targets, ample spacing
- **Flexible layouts** — Stack on mobile, grid on desktop

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
  {flights.map(f => <FlightCard key={f.id} flight={f} />)}
</div>
```

---

## Anti-Slop Directive

**Before generating ANY code for a new screen, read `design-direction.md` AND `design-tokens.json` in full.**

Slop is generic UI that ignores AirThere's identity:

❌ Default Shadcn colors (blue-600, gray-200) instead of AirThere tokens
❌ Placeholder grays (#ccc, #999) instead of OKLCH surface palette
❌ Lorem Ipsum instead of real travel data
❌ Inconsistent border-radius (mix of sizes instead of unified system)
❌ Missing dark mode variants
❌ 40×40pt touch targets (too small; min 44pt)
❌ Copy that doesn't match AirThere's tone (should be calm, transparent, warm)
❌ Colors with 3:1 contrast instead of 4.5:1

**Quality gates before pushing code:**

✅ All colors from `design-tokens.json`
✅ All spacing from `design-tokens.json` (multiples of 4px)
✅ All typography from design system (16px body, 20px heading, etc.)
✅ Touch targets ≥44×44pt
✅ Color contrast ≥4.5:1
✅ Dark mode tested and working
✅ ARIA labels present for complex components
✅ Loading, error, empty states implemented
✅ Authentic travel data (no Lorem Ipsum)
✅ Copy matches tone (calm, transparent, warm, family-centric as appropriate)

