## How to Test

```bash
npm run test              # Vitest unit tests
npm run test:a11y        # Accessibility tests (axe-core)
npm run test:watch       # Watch mode
npm run lint             # ESLint
npm run type-check       # TypeScript strict
npm run build            # Production build
```

Every screen must include:
- Unit tests for all components
- Accessibility audit (axe-core)
- Responsive snapshot tests (320px, 768px, 1024px)

---

## Key Constraints

| Constraint | Target | Why |
|-----------|--------|-----|
| **WCAG 2.1 AA** | 100% compliance | Legal + moral imperative |
| **Core Web Vitals** | LCP <2.5s, FID <100ms, CLS <0.1 | Performance baseline |
| **Mobile-first** | Perfect at 320px | Device-inclusive design |
| **Responsive** | Up to 1440px+ | Tablet + desktop support |
| **NPS 60+** | Industry-leading | Year 1 success goal |
| **Booking <30% abandon** | Drop-off prevention | Revenue impact |
| **Family seating 98%** | Guaranteed placement | Core family promise |

---

## Key Principles

**Read Design Direction First.** Every time. Before building any new screen, read `07.5-design-direction/design-direction.md` and `design-tokens.json` in full. This is the source of truth for colors, spacing, typography, and visual identity.

**Mock Data is Real Data.** Use actual airline codes (AA, BA, SQ), airport codes (JFK, LHR, SIN), realistic prices. No Lorem Ipsum. Travelers need authentic content to validate the experience.

**Personas are Real People.** Alexandra isn't a generic "premium user." Marcus isn't a generic "business user." The Chen Family isn't a generic "budget user." Design for their actual needs, psychographics, and success indicators.

**Accessibility is Beauty.** WCAG 2.1 AA isn't a constraint; it's a feature. High contrast improves legibility for everyone. Clear focus indicators help all users. Sufficient spacing reduces errors. The most beautiful design serves everyone equally well.

**State Management Matters.** Every component has loading, error, and empty states. Never show a bare skeleton. Never show an unhelpful error. Every state is an opportunity to reinforce AirThere's brand of anticipatory calm.

**Dark Mode Works.** Test every component in dark mode. The color system supports it. Every `bg-primary-500` needs a `dark:bg-primary-400` variant. No exceptions.

